# Git Workflow

- `main` — production-ready, never commit directly
- `development` — integration branch, merges come here first
- Feature branches: `dev-NNN-brief-description` (from `development`)

# Commit Style

```
[dev-NNN] Short imperative description (50 chars max)

Optional body explaining the why, not the what.
```

# Feature Flow

1. `git checkout -b dev-NNN-description development`
2. Implement with small, focused commits
3. Run `mix precommit` before pushing
4. `git push -u origin dev-NNN-description`
5. PR targets `development` (never `main`)

# Rules

- Never push directly to `main` or `development`
- One logical change per branch — keep PRs small
- Run `mix precommit` before every push
